Monti has managed to form a government in less than three days, much less time than normal, while Italy is struggling with a political and financial crisis that has driven the cost of debt to an unbearable level.
The new government, led by former EU Commissioner Monti, must adopt a harsh savings package called for by Euro politicians to regain the shattered trust in Italy.
