My friends have always gone to surf to Costa Rica and Nicaragua. Together with Mexico, the excellent areas are for surfing. In this way, we learned about people who love surfing.
With a look at the tour you have offered giant shows with many songs.
What are your plans for the event in Costa Rica?
Since we have never played there, we do not set ourselves any limits.
We will try to give the best possible show with many different songs. We want to play a few songs from each album and provide our fans with a good and versatile repertoire.
You never repeat your repertoire.
- Why? - Yeah.
I think that’s partly because we have nine records and can play more than 120 songs, and everyone likes a different song, so the decision we’re going to play isn’t easy.
If we record two or three songs that we haven’t played for a long time, we can better maintain our concentration and surprise us because they remind us of the reasons why we liked these songs, otherwise they might be forgotten.
